<h1>Chris Winters</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://cwinters.com/now/">cwinters.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Pittsburgh
PA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Developer and Engineering Manager at Turnitin
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
Make things work on the internet, help teams do the same.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Making software to solve problems is a wonderful job -- I get to learn about how people do their jobs and help them be better at what they do. And I get to create things from thin air to do so.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Everything winds up better if you step back a few and look again.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Paul Ford: “How to Be Polite” (it's hard for me to pick just one anything by him)
</p>

